:R-HSA-159236  a            owl:NamedIndividual , obo:GO_0006406 ;
        rdfs:comment        "Transport of mRNA from the nucleus to the cytoplasm, where it is translated into protein, is highly selective and closely coupled to correct RNA processing. This coupling is achieved by the nuclear pore complex, which recognizes and transports only completed mRNAs." ;
